      • startMapReduceOperation

        public boolean startMapReduceOperation()
        This method starts a map-reduce operation, and it must be called after the preliminary setup process has been done. Once this method starts a map-reduce operation, it does not start any other map-reduce operation until the current task is finished, and its result is retrieved.
        Specified by:
        startMapReduceOperation in interface MapReducer<T,E>
        Returns:
        boolean returns true if starts a map-reduce operation successfully, false otherwise.

      • map

        protected abstract void map()
        This method provides user-specified parallel approach for performing the tasks. Each parallel task must submit their result using the method. The submitResult method, sends every two submitted result to for parallel reduction.

        Note: Invoking this method by user, must be done through the public method.
        Since:
        2016

      • parallelReduce

        protected abstract void parallelReduce(T t1,
                                       T t2)
        This method provides user-specified parallel approach for performing reductions as parallel tasks. A user must submit their results back to method.
        Parameters:
        t1 - first instance of the result, returned from one of the tasks
        t2 - second instance of the result, returned from one of the tasks
        Since:
